# Flutter Development

- Prefer widget composition over deep inheritance.
- Keep widget inputs immutable (`final` fields, `const` constructors when possible).
- Keep `build()` side-effect free; no I/O, logging loops, or mutation in `build()`.
- Use `setState()` only for local UI state; move shared/business state out of widgets.
- Prefer `async`/`await` over chained `then()`/`catchError()`.
- Respect null safety; avoid `!` unless correctness is proven by control flow.
- Keep code formatter/lints clean (`dart format`, `flutter_lints`).
- Add or update tests for behavior changes (`test/`, widget tests for UI logic).
